---
title: 'Every Day Is a Draft'
date: '2026-03-05'
category: 'thought'
excerpt: 'You are allowed to rewrite yourself.'
---

Every day is a first draft.

You are not required to be the same person you were yesterday. You are not bound by the version of yourself that made mistakes last week, last year, or ten years ago.

The fool knows this better than anyone — that the whole point of wandering is that you are always arriving somewhere new.

Rewrite yourself as often as you need. Just make sure the next draft is more honest than the last.
